  {
    "discussion_id": "2243185512",
    "pr_number": 32325,
    "pr_file": "libs/text-splitters/pyproject.toml",
    "created_at": "2025-07-30T16:07:04+00:00",
    "commented_code": "[tool.ruff]\n target-version = \"py39\"\n \n+\n [tool.ruff.lint]\n-select = [\"E\", \"F\", \"FBT\", \"I\", \"UP\", \"PGH003\", \"T201\", \"D\"]\n-ignore = [\"D100\",]\n+select = [ \"ALL\",]",
    "repo_full_name": "langchain-ai/langchain",
    "discussion_comments": [
      {
        "comment_id": "2243185512",
        "repo_full_name": "langchain-ai/langchain",
        "pr_number": 32325,
        "pr_file": "libs/text-splitters/pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "2243185512",
        "commented_code": "@@ -60,11 +60,45 @@ ignore_missing_imports = \"True\"\n [tool.ruff]\n target-version = \"py39\"\n \n+\n [tool.ruff.lint]\n-select = [\"E\", \"F\", \"FBT\", \"I\", \"UP\", \"PGH003\", \"T201\", \"D\"]\n-ignore = [\"D100\",]\n+select = [ \"ALL\",]",
        "comment_created_at": "2025-07-30T16:07:04+00:00",
        "comment_author": "mdrxy",
        "comment_body": "I'm still against selecting `ALL` without scoping `fixable`:\r\n* New ruff versions may introduce rules that automatically \"fix\" code in unintended ways\r\n* Auto-fixes for complex rules might introduce bugs while \"improving\" code or making it less readable\r\n\r\nSo perhaps we keep `ALL` under `select` but manually opt new rules into `fixable` (not selecting `ALL`)",
        "pr_file_module": null
      },
      {
        "comment_id": "2243186024",
        "repo_full_name": "langchain-ai/langchain",
        "pr_number": 32325,
        "pr_file": "libs/text-splitters/pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "2243185512",
        "commented_code": "@@ -60,11 +60,45 @@ ignore_missing_imports = \"True\"\n [tool.ruff]\n target-version = \"py39\"\n \n+\n [tool.ruff.lint]\n-select = [\"E\", \"F\", \"FBT\", \"I\", \"UP\", \"PGH003\", \"T201\", \"D\"]\n-ignore = [\"D100\",]\n+select = [ \"ALL\",]",
        "comment_created_at": "2025-07-30T16:07:18+00:00",
        "comment_author": "mdrxy",
        "comment_body": "Other wise this PR looks good",
        "pr_file_module": null
      },
      {
        "comment_id": "2244065593",
        "repo_full_name": "langchain-ai/langchain",
        "pr_number": 32325,
        "pr_file": "libs/text-splitters/pyproject.toml",
        "discussion_id": "2243185512",
        "commented_code": "@@ -60,11 +60,45 @@ ignore_missing_imports = \"True\"\n [tool.ruff]\n target-version = \"py39\"\n \n+\n [tool.ruff.lint]\n-select = [\"E\", \"F\", \"FBT\", \"I\", \"UP\", \"PGH003\", \"T201\", \"D\"]\n-ignore = [\"D100\",]\n+select = [ \"ALL\",]",
        "comment_created_at": "2025-07-30T23:44:34+00:00",
        "comment_author": "cbornet",
        "comment_body": "Ruff doesn't introduce new rules between patch versions (https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/versioning/) and we pin the minor version (currently 0.12).\r\nSo there's no difference with a long list of rules.\r\nI can put the full list but I think using `ALL` makes the conf simpler.",
        "pr_file_module": null
      }
    ]
  },
